        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/s/c4cdca/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2026-02-01T19:20:09.061Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Excellent feature that, unfortunately, I donâ€™t think Iâ€™m likely to use often in the current implementation for two reasons:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Most importantly, having a whole line of screen space in the application taken up by the pin information bar makes it unwieldy and distracting for me, instead of ensuring I can find the things I donâ€™t want to forget easily so that I can take it off my mental plate it causes it to exert the pressure of keeping it in mind the whole time Iâ€™m in that chat.<br>\nI think that thereâ€™s a use case for that presentation for some people so a toggle or ability to collapse and expand it from the horizontal ellipsis (meatballs menu) button (vertical ellipsis/kebab menu) in mobile might make the most sense.</li>\n<li>Three pins, with it being easy to auto-replace oldest when adding new, is far too few for my use cases and far too easy to mess up an important pin on accident, itâ€™s not completely without purpose as it currently is but my most immediate use case for it would need at least double that at six pins in order to be a functional replacement for my current system.<br>\nA method to flag pins for protection from auto-delete would also remove some manual management steps when dealing with a mixture of â€˜running updateâ€™ and â€˜standard reference informationâ€™ style pins at the same time.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>I hope that this feature receives further attention in the future as itâ€™s quite handy and could conveniently replace keyword search based tagging I currently use for some purposes.<br>\nThanks to everyone involved for all their hard work on Signal!</p>",
